The paper deals with algorithms for computing shortest cycles in weighted graphs, which is a problem in graph theory and algorithms. The paper uses techniques from data structures (such as distance oracles), computational geometry (such as geometric hitting sets), discrete mathematics (such as graph theory), numerical analysis (such as polynomially bounded weights), and game theory (such as approximation algorithms). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper involves numerical analysis and optimization, which suggest sub-categories cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.GT (Game Theory).
